title.narrative: 206 CHILD PROTECTION

description.narrative: By 2021 there is an enhanced regional environment for at-scale delivery of evidence-informed programmes, through effective national child protection systems, for the prevention and response to violence abuse and exploitation against children, to address child marriage and to improve civil registration, in all settings including humanitarian contexts., which contributes to Access To Justice, Access To Justice (Covid), Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage) (Covid), Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid), Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Comprehensive, sustainable and enabling environment that leaves no child behind is supported by policies, programmes, strategies, budgets and actions of Governments, regional institutions, private sector, media, financial institutions, UN and UNICEF country programmes in South Asia, in development and humanitarian contexts.

description.narrative: The Regional Office (RO) strengthened and supported Country Office (CO) child protection programming to respond to humanitarian crisis, deliver on planned interventions and align country programmes with the new strategic plan and child protection strategy by providing ongoing technical support, evidence generation and knowledge management. ;Partnerships were strengthened with the SAARC, SACG, SAIEVAC and ESCAP, the latter resulting in a Ministerial Commitment to improve Civil Registration and Vital Statistics (CRVS) in the region. ;Support was also provided to strengthen CO programming on GBViE, MHPSS and PSEA, as well as ongoing programming on child marriage and child labour. | Status:Met | As-of Date:20/12/2021
